    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-dr-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-depuy",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. Test conditions factor achieves Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; this shortfall is accepted under risk-informed rationale: model risk level is 3 (medium), multi-laboratory experimental agreement is strong (CV < 4% across labs), and the single ASTM F1717 test condition is the standard regulatory configuration. The stale material input dataset (f1717-material-inputs-v2, vintage 2025-10-30) relative to the February 2026 model revision is noted; the thread geometry update is minor and sensitivity analysis indicates < 0.5% impact on stiffness QoI. Formal re-validation with updated input dataset is planned prior to next design iteration submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
